srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/w3rvVVZkDrWLeIQKtP4gKtKWLck=/375x250/filters:format(webp)/90f929a8-328f-4083-9846-1d23b98eed34--2023-0213march-key-stories_drinks_pouring-drink_mid_1x1-4x5_mark-weinberg_0853.jpg, https://images.food52.com/EvUz6wbquWfS-hf4XQoh8WD8TjI=/750x500/filters:format(webp)/90f929a8-328f-4083-9846-1d23b98eed34--2023-0213march-key-stories_drinks_pouring-drink_mid_1x1-4x5_mark-weinberg_0853.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003cimg srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/FovY0137j9v94oCafGoi1wP18kg=/375x250/90f929a8-328f-4083-9846-1d23b98eed34--2023-0213march-key-stories_drinks_pouring-drink_mid_1x1-4x5_mark-weinberg_0853.jpg, https://images.food52.com/pSXe2hXpSL0RCCqCkceAQtdnzl0=/750x500/90f929a8-328f-4083-9846-1d23b98eed34--2023-0213march-key-stories_drinks_pouring-drink_mid_1x1-4x5_mark-weinberg_0853.jpg 2x\" alt=\"Person pouring wine into a glass\" width=\"1348\" height=\"898\" data-pin-media=\"https://images.food52.com/VrGGCrxKsrzLua8Uj5U7HSs_-Os=/2000x2000/90f929a8-328f-4083-9846-1d23b98eed34--2023-0213march-key-stories_drinks_pouring-drink_mid_1x1-4x5_mark-weinberg_0853.jpg\" data-pin-url=\"https://food52.com/blog/28544-come-on-over-how-to-beat-hosting-stress\" data-pin-description=\"How to Fight Pre-Party Stress, And More Hosting Advice From Our Editor on Food52\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/FovY0137j9v94oCafGoi1wP18kg=/375x250/90f929a8-328f-4083-9846-1d23b98eed34--2023-0213march-key-stories_drinks_pouring-drink_mid_1x1-4x5_mark-weinberg_0853.jpg, https://images.food52.com/pSXe2hXpSL0RCCqCkceAQtdnzl0=/750x500/90f929a8-328f-4083-9846-1d23b98eed34--2023-0213march-key-stories_drinks_pouring-drink_mid_1x1-4x5_mark-weinberg_0853.jpg 2x\" src=\"https://images.food52.com/VrGGCrxKsrzLua8Uj5U7HSs_-Os=/2000x2000/90f929a8-328f-4083-9846-1d23b98eed34--2023-0213march-key-stories_drinks_pouring-drink_mid_1x1-4x5_mark-weinberg_0853.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePhoto by Mark Weinberg\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003c/section\u003e\n\n\n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n          \u003cdiv\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eWelcome to the latest edition of \u003cstrong\u003eCome On Over\u003c/strong\u003e, Food52 editorial director Julie Vadnal\u0026#39;s newsletter that\u0026#39;s all about hosting gatherings big and small—without losing your cool. Got company? \u003ca href=\"https://food52.attn.tv/p/HBo/comeonover\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSign up here\u003c/a\u003e for her emails.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n              \u003chr/\u003e\n\n              \u003cp\u003eWhen I first starting having people over in my 20s, my biggest fear was always: Will there be enough food? As a result, I’d make so many dishes that I wouldn’t have time to shower, and guests would arrive to a home filled with entirely too many appetizers—and a frazzled, cranky host. Since then, I’ve learned that, as the person hosting, you set the tone. The better prepared you are, the more relaxed everyone will be, including yourself.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n              \u003cp\u003eNo one is staring at the stain on your rug, or the askew art on your walls. Vacuum the floors, make your bed, and wipe down the bathroom—then turn off the overheads. Candlelight, even the LED kind, just makes everything (and everyone) look better.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n\n  \n\n              \n              \u003cp\u003eYou do not want to be stuck at the stovetop during your own party, trust me. For a dinner party, make a meal you can pop in the oven when friends arrive: slow-roasted salmon with a salad is a favorite of mine. For a cocktail party, one giant grazing board can be a full dinner.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \n              \n\n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button\" data-pin-do=\"buttonPin\" data-pin-media=\"\" data-pin-custom=\"true\" data-ga-event=\"inP